1 Why do we convert continuous values into categories?

 To make data easier to understand and use
 Example: Instead of numbers, we use labels like Gold, Silver, Bronze

2 What is the difference between business segmentation and technical bucketing?

 Business segmentation → based on business rules (like revenue, strategy)
 Technical bucketing → based on data ranges or algorithms

3 When would fixed thresholds fail?

 When data changes or is uneven
 Example: If most customers spend very low or very high, fixed rules won’t work well

4  How does quantile-based segmentation differ from fixed rules?

 Fixed rules → predefined values (like >10000)
 Quantile → based on actual data distribution (top %, middle %, bottom %)

5 Which method would you use in real-world projects?

 Mostly quantile-based segmentation
 Because it adapts to data and gives balanced groups